            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3ETo%20obey%20is%20better%20than%20sacrifice.%20This%20simple%20statement%20contains%20the%20secret%20to%20pleasing%20God.%20Rebellion%20began%20with%20the%20devil's%20asserting%20his%20own%20will%20and%20making%20his%20own%20decisions.%20Saul's%20problems%20started%20when%20he%20no%20longer%20was%20small%20in%20his%20own%20eyes%20but%2C%20in%20pride%2C%20began%20to%20make%20decisions%20apart%20from%20God's%20will.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ERebellion%20and%20arrogance%20tell%20us%20that%20we%20know%20more%20than%20God%20does%20and%20that%20our%20ways%20are%20above%20His%20ways.%20The%20Lord%2C%20however%2C%20doesn't%20need%20us%20to%20think%20for%20Him%2C%20but%20only%20to%20carry%20out%20what%20He%20commands.%20He%20found%20this%20trait%20in%20David%2C%20a%20young%20shepherd%20boy%20who%20possessed%20a%20heart%20to%20obey%20Him%20fully%20(1%20Samuel%2016%3A7).%20Because%20of%20David's%20pure%20heart%2C%20God%20took%20the%20kingdom%20from%20Saul%20and%20awarded%20it%20to%20David.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EJesus'%20life%20was%20powerful%20because%20He%20never%20once%20asserted%20His%20own%20will.%20In%20the%20wilderness%2C%20during%20His%20ministry%2C%20at%20Gethsemane%2C%20and%20on%20the%20cross%2C%20Jesus%20perfectly%20obeyed.%20So%2C%20too%2C%20does%20our%20power%20with%20God%20rest%20in%20our%20obedience%20to%20Him.%20We%20must%20always%20remember%20this%3A%20The%20important%20thing%20is%20not%20that%20we%20have%20done%20something%20for%20God%2C%20but%20that%20we%20have%20done%20what%20God%20wanted%20us%20to%20do!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
